{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 08:55:57.660671", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: I’ve pulled the BGP tables for all four leaf routers. At a glance they all appear to have learned the same set of prefixes (10.0.0.0/24 through 10.0.6.0/24) and are using the expected next‑hop IPs for each peer. However, without a symptom or a specific question it’s hard to know whether something is actually wrong.\\n\\nCould you let me know:\\n\\n1. **What problem are you observing?**  \\n   - Is there a loss of connectivity between certain hosts?  \\n   - Are some routes missing or incorrectly advertised?  \\n   - Are you seeing unexpected traffic patterns or performance degradation?\\n\\n2. **Which hosts or links are affected?**  \\n   - Are the issues confined to a particular leaf, spine, or end‑host?  \\n   - Are there specific subnets that are unreachable?\\n\\n3. **Any recent changes?**  \\n   - New BGP peers, route filters, ACLs, or changes to the P4 program on the bmv2 switch?  \\n   - Updates to the FRR configuration or the switch firmware?\\n\\nOnce I have that context I can drill down—checking reachability, route tables, interface stats, or switch counters—to pinpoint the anomaly, localize the faulty device(s), and identify the root cause., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a5d5ce54-136f-4a98-bb99-854983e41c3a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
